node.text:
Why is clinical research important?

Essential oils contain a variety of constituents and clinical research is a tool to show how the chemistry of essential oils may affect human physiology.

Before being tested clinically, doTERRA® oils are tested for purity to ensure contaminants that could be harmful or reduce the effectiveness of the oil are not present.

Listen to Dr. Nicole Stevens discuss essential oil research and more on Fox 13!

Learn more at https://loom.ly/jZmOT6Q

node.text:
In our quest to provide you with the purest essential oils, dōTERRA® puts every batch through an exhaustive testing protocol of physical, chemical, and stability testing procedures that ensure our oils are free of synthetics, additives, and harmful contaminants.

Our quality testing is meticulous so you can trust every bottle of oil you open is truly a “gift of the earth.” 

To learn more about what goes on at QC, watch the short video above then let us know what you think!

#doterrascience #doterra #essentialoils #science #qualitycontrol #pursuewhatspure

node.text:
Solvent extraction is a complex method of essential oil collection. Plant material is washed with a solvent and then filtered, leaving behind a "concrete." Concretes contain all of the potent fragrant compounds of the plant as well as other lipid soluble compounds. After the concrete is processed with a second solvent, only the pure absolute remains. An absolute is different from an essential oil because they can contain both aromatic and non-aromatic chemical constituents.

The jasmine absolute used in dōTERRA® Jasmine Touch is produced using this method. To learn more, watch the video above!

What did you learn? Comment and let us know!
⠀
#doterrascience #doterra #essentialoils #science

node.text:
How well do you know your endocrine system❓

The endocrine system is made up of the glands and tissues that produce and secrete hormones, which act as chemical messengers that can travel through the bloodstream and interact with cellular targets within a particular tissue to regulate activity. 

The brain is an endocrine hub, housing important hormone-generating structures like the pituitary gland, pineal gland, and hypothalamus. Appetite, sleep cycles, and emotion are just some of the processes regulated by these three endocrine glands. 

Promoting healthy endocrine responses benefits your overall health. Inhale Rosemary or Lavender essential to help you relax in a stressful situation. You can also apply Clary Sage or ClaryCalm® to the abdomen for a soothing massage during your menstrual cycle.

Tap the 🔗 in our bio to learn more.
